The paper discusses a framework for designing autonomous agents, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of preferences and actions in the framework suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The mention of formal representations and temporal logic indicates a focus on logic and verification (cs.LO), while the overall goal of designing a complex system suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
